WEBVTT

00:10.577 --> 00:13.113
Gabriel Wyath, 26.

00:13.247 --> 00:14.931
Engineering student...

00:14.965 --> 00:16.867
diagnosed about five years ago.

00:17.167 --> 00:20.118
Delusions began to grow
increasingly vivid and violent,

00:20.136 --> 00:22.721
eventually requiring
hospitalization.

00:22.755 --> 00:25.290
Gabe has successfully
masked his issues for so long

00:25.308 --> 00:27.292
that by the time
that anyone was aware

00:27.310 --> 00:29.094
of the extent of his problems,

00:29.128 --> 00:31.096
his delusions had convinced him

00:31.131 --> 00:33.482
to try and blow up
a government building.

00:33.516 --> 00:35.150
So what are we looking for

00:35.185 --> 00:37.019
when we make a diagnosis
of schizophrenia?

00:37.070 --> 00:38.403
Steph?

00:38.438 --> 00:39.905
Well, many patients

00:39.939 --> 00:40.939
<i>develop a routine</i>

00:40.973 --> 00:42.374
<i>to help them maintain</i>

00:42.408 --> 00:43.692
<i>the illusion of control.</i>

00:43.726 --> 00:44.843
Double Americano.

00:44.878 --> 00:45.944
Extra shot. Skim milk.

00:45.979 --> 00:47.029
Extra hot. Thanks.

00:48.565 --> 00:49.448
Black coffee?

00:49.482 --> 00:51.350
<i>Despite this, they</i>

00:51.384 --> 00:55.420
<i>outwardly exhibit disorganized</i>
<i>or odd behavior.</i>

00:55.455 --> 00:56.672
I don't think
that's what I ordered.

00:56.706 --> 00:58.423
<i>Which can lead to confusion</i>

00:58.458 --> 01:00.325
and agitation.

01:00.343 --> 01:03.128
Where did you put
the Alderman file?

01:03.162 --> 01:05.964
Who the hell is Alderman?

01:10.169 --> 01:11.136
See?

01:11.170 --> 01:12.838
Right where I said it was.

01:13.940 --> 01:16.391
<i>They might suffer from</i>
<i>coexisting sleep disorders,</i>

01:16.442 --> 01:18.944
<i>including insomnia.</i>

01:18.978 --> 01:20.812
The majority of cases
become unstable

01:20.846 --> 01:21.864
without medication.

01:21.898 --> 01:23.181
Good.

01:23.199 --> 01:24.900
The issue lies in what happens

01:24.951 --> 01:27.186
when a patient
refuses treatment.

01:27.220 --> 01:30.522
<i>Many will endure</i>
<i>confusion, anger</i>

01:30.540 --> 01:32.407
and risk harm to themselves
and others,

01:32.458 --> 01:34.526
<i>all in an effort</i>
<i>to cling to things</i>

01:34.544 --> 01:35.627
<i>that only they see</i>

01:35.662 --> 01:37.963
<i>and understand.</i>

01:37.997 --> 01:40.549
That's what makes
these patients so dangerous.

01:40.583 --> 01:42.050
The delusions
that drive them

01:42.085 --> 01:44.636
also convince them
to try to hide the depth

01:44.671 --> 01:45.721
of their problems.

01:45.755 --> 01:47.422
Our challenge is to...

01:47.473 --> 01:49.141
try to find a way

01:49.175 --> 01:51.927
<i>to help someone</i>
<i>who doesn't want it.</i>

01:51.961 --> 01:54.563
<i>The risk lies in...</i>

01:54.597 --> 01:58.417
<i>the damage</i>
<i>they can do if we fail.</i>

01:59.419 --> 02:01.603
<i>So tell me how this works.</i>

02:01.654 --> 02:03.655
<i>I'm awake with my wife,</i>
<i>and I close me eyes,</i>

02:03.690 --> 02:06.057
<i>I open them...</i>
<i>I'm awake with my son.</i>

02:06.075 --> 02:08.560
And this has been happening
since the accident?

02:10.747 --> 02:12.714
<i>So you began</i>
<i>working on one case</i>

02:12.749 --> 02:13.582
<i>here in reality,</i>

02:13.616 --> 02:15.000
<i>and then suddenly</i>

02:15.034 --> 02:16.285
you begin working another case

02:16.336 --> 02:18.120
<i>there, in your dream.</i>

02:18.154 --> 02:20.455
<i>It all feels</i>
<i>completely real to me.</i>

02:20.506 --> 02:22.574
<i>You can't tell</i>
<i>whether you're awake or asleep</i>

02:22.592 --> 02:23.709
at this very moment?

02:23.743 --> 02:25.394
<i>Well I can assure</i>
<i>you, Detective Britten,</i>

02:25.428 --> 02:26.595
this is not a dream.

02:26.629 --> 02:29.148
That's exactly
what the other shrink said.

